headline: Occidental CEO Forecasts $60 Oil Through 2026, Bullish on Long-Term Outlook
summary: Occidental Petroleum CEO Vicki Hollub expects oil prices to remain steady between $58 and $62 per barrel through 2026, with stronger gains to follow in the longer term
